    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sets of containers and implements fitted in a box or tray, to store and prepare ingredients for the practice of betel chewing. A typical set might include containers for storing betel leaves, sliced areca nuts, lime paste and gambier, a nut cutter, a spatula for scooping the paste, a mortar and a spittoon.   </Note_Text>
